---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "I Mapped Every Road I've Been On in Seattle";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description="I Mapped Every Road I've Been On in Seattle">
  <!-- Intro section -->
  <section class="explorer-prose explorer-intro">
    <div class="prose-container">
      <h1 class="explorer-title">I Mapped Every Road I've Been On in Seattle</h1>
      <p>
        After living in Seattle for more than a couple of years, I ended up going to the Arboretum on a random Thursday. I had driven by it several dozen times, seen it on maps, and probably mentioned it in conversations, but I had not really been there. When I finally went, it made me wonder: how much of Seattle had I actually seen?
      </p>
      <p>
        Not whether I had done the standard Seattle things, or how many restaurants I had tried. I mean more literally: which streets had I actually been on? Cities can trick you this way because you know your grocery store, the fastest way home, and the annoying intersection to avoid, but your life in a city is not evenly distributed.
      </p>
      <p>
        I am, unfortunately, a sucker for nostalgia. So despite the obvious privacy horror of it all, I have Google Location History turned on. It is invasive and occasionally unsettling, but it is also a strangely vivid way to revisit the past and the Timeline data is perfectly suited to reconstruct my exploration of Seattle over time. 
      </p>  
      <p>  
        The result is heavily biased toward places I drove, because that is when GPS was most consistently active. 
      </p>
      <p>  
        As you scroll below, the city slowly fills in as part map and part personal diary.
      </p>
      <p class="scroll-hint">Scroll to begin &darr;</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Map scroll section -->
  <div class="scroll-container" id="scrollContainer">
    <div class="map-viewport" id="mapViewport">
      <!-- Canvas renderer. All map drawing (roads, water, terrain) happens
           here via the Canvas 2D API. Labels are positioned HTML for
           crisp text rendering. -->
      <canvas id="mapCanvas" class="map-layer"></canvas>

      <!-- Label overlay layer. Positions are computed per frame from
           state-SVG coords via the camera transform. data-sx/data-sy are
           positions in the state SVG coordinate system. -->
      <div class="map-overlay" id="mapOverlay">
        <span class="city-label" data-lng="-122.3321" data-lat="47.6062" data-size="0.014">Seattle</span>
        <span class="city-label" data-lng="-122.2015" data-lat="47.6101" data-size="0.011">Bellevue</span>
        <span class="state-label state-label-city" data-sx="2465" data-sy="1898">Seattle</span>
        <span class="state-label state-label-park" data-sx="1218" data-sy="1651">Olympic<br>National Park</span>
        <span class="state-label state-label-park" data-sx="3026" data-sy="2520">Mt. Rainier<br>National Park</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Right-edge fade: replaces the SVG mask. Visible only during
           state phases; opacity toggled by JS. -->
      <div class="state-edge-fade" id="stateEdgeFade"></div>
      <div class="timeline-sidebar" id="timelineSidebar">
        <div class="timeline-track" id="timelineTrack">
          <div class="timeline-indicator" id="timelineIndicator">
            <span class="timeline-date-label" id="timelineDateLabel"></span>
            <span class="timeline-indicator-line"></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Horizontal timeline: mobile-only. Pinned to the bottom of the
           sticky map viewport so it anchors the bottom letterbox band and
           gives the user date context during all phases. -->
      <div class="mobile-timeline" id="mobileTimeline">
        <div class="mobile-timeline-track" id="mobileTimelineTrack">
          <div class="mobile-timeline-indicator" id="mobileTimelineIndicator">
            <span class="mobile-timeline-date" id="mobileTimelineDate"></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="loading-msg" id="loadingMsg">Loading road network...</div>
    </div>
    <div class="scroll-spacer"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Outro section -->
  <section class="explorer-prose explorer-outro">
    <div class="prose-container">
      <h2>How I made this</h2>
      <p>
        Google Timeline logs your location pretty frequently and for me that's something like 1.8 million GPS pings across several years.
      </p>
      <p>
        Plotting them raw is unreadable; what you want is each ping snapped to an actual road. So I pulled the road network of every drivable street from OpenStreetMap (~80,000+ edges), and Washington's highways for the state view (~20,000+ edges).
        I mapped each GPS ping to its nearest road to get the edges I directly drove on (40%<span class="reference-note" tabindex="0" aria-label="The rest is dominated by tiny edges of tertiary roads">[1]<span class="reference-note-content" role="tooltip">The rest is dominated by tiny edges of tertiary roads</span></span> of the map).
      </p>
      <p>
        The interesting trick is filling in the gaps. GPS sampling is irregular: sometimes my phone drops a ping every minute, sometimes every fifteen. On a long highway drive, that can leave miles of dark road between two lit points even though I obviously drove it. So for every pair of consecutive pings, I lit up the shortest route between consecutive if they happened within a few minutes of each other.
      </p>
      <p>
        For the animation, I tag every visited edge with the date I first drove it, sort the whole thing chronologically, and chop it into equal-count buckets rather than equal slices of time. The scrubber walks through "the next slice of map that lit up" rather than equal slices of time or else the whole thing would be dominated by my commute to work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style is:global>
  /* Candidate fonts for the state-zoom labels — referenced via --label-font */
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;1,400&family=EB+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;1,400&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500&family=Spectral:ital,wght@0,300;0,500;1,300&display=swap');

  /* ============================================================
     PALETTE CONFIG — swap palettes by changing :root variables.
     To switch: comment out the active palette, uncomment another.
     ============================================================ */

  /* Parchment Atlas — off-white page, sepia roads, dusty blue water.
     Matches the prose-section bg so map + text feel continuous. */
  :root {
    --map-bg: #F2EBDD;                          /* matches .explorer-prose bg */
    --road-base: #B8A38A;                       /* muted sepia — recedes against bg */
    --road-highlight: #1F1208;                  /* black ink — letterpress contrast vs muted base */
    --text-primary: #2A2218;                    /* deep warm black */
    --text-secondary: rgba(60, 50, 38, 0.55);   /* muted sepia */
    --water-fill: #B6CFE0;                      /* dusty blue */
    --water-stroke: #88A4B8;                    /* deeper blue */
    --terrain-tint: #8A7B68;                    /* warm grey-brown */
    --label-halo: rgba(242, 235, 221, 0.85);    /* parchment-colored stroke halo */
    --label-font: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
  }

  /* Ink & Teal — cool mist, dark slate grid, vivid teal traces
  :root {
    --map-bg: #F0F4F8;
    --road-base: #3D4F5F;
    --road-highlight: #0D9488;
    --text-primary: #334155;
    --text-secondary: #94A3B8;
    --water-fill: #C8DCE8;
    --water-stroke: #A8C4D4;
  }
  */

  /* Soft Fog — cool mist, light slate roads, teal highlights
  :root {
    --map-bg: #F0F4F8;
    --road-base: #CBD5E1;
    --road-highlight: #0D9488;
    --text-primary: #334155;
    --text-secondary: #94A3B8;
    --water-fill: #C8DCE8;
    --water-stroke: #A8C4D4;
  }
  */

  /* Midnight Ink — indigo-black, dusty purple roads, amber highlights
  :root {
    --map-bg: #0F0E17;
    --road-base: #594E78;
    --road-highlight: #E8AE68;
    --text-primary: #FFFFFE;
    --text-secondary: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    --water-fill: #1A1A2E;
    --water-stroke: #252545;
  }
  */

  /* Deep Forest — dark canopy, sage roads, firefly amber highlights
  :root {
    --map-bg: #0B1A14;
    --road-base: #2D5A3D;
    --road-highlight: #FFB347;
    --text-primary: #E6EBD8;
    --text-secondary: rgba(230, 235, 216, 0.5);
    --water-fill: #0A2018;
    --water-stroke: #153028;
  }
  */

  /* Original — dark navy, blue roads, cyan highlights
  :root {
    --map-bg: #000817;
    --road-base: #0466C8;
    --road-highlight: #00FFFF;
    --text-primary: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    --text-secondary: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    --water-fill: #001030;
    --water-stroke: #001845;
  }
  */

  /* ============================================================ */

  /* Override BaseLayout container to allow full-width map */
  main.container {
    max-width: 100% !important;
    padding: 0 !important;
    margin: 0 !important;
  }

  /* Prose sections (intro & outro) — off-white, decoupled from the dark
     map palette. Map stays dark; only the surrounding text panels are
     light. */
  .explorer-prose {
    --prose-bg: #F2EBDD;
    --prose-heading: #1F1A14;
    --prose-body: #443A30;
    --prose-muted: #7D7060;
    background: var(--prose-bg);
    color: var(--prose-body);
  }

  .prose-container {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .explorer-title {
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 2.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--prose-heading);
  }

  .explorer-prose p {
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--prose-body);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .reference-note {
    position: relative;
    display: inline-block;
    margin-left: 0.12em;
    color: var(--prose-heading);
    cursor: help;
    font-size: 0.65em;
    line-height: 1;
    vertical-align: super;
  }

  .reference-note-content {
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    bottom: calc(100% + 0.6rem);
    z-index: 10;
    width: max-content;
    max-width: 16rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.7rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(31, 26, 20, 0.15);
    border-radius: 0.45rem;
    background: #FFFBF1;
    color: var(--prose-body);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    text-align: left;
    box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(31, 26, 20, 0.1);
    transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(0.2rem);
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    transition: opacity 140ms ease, transform 140ms ease;
  }

  .reference-note:hover .reference-note-content,
  .reference-note:focus .reference-note-content {
    transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(0);
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .explorer-prose h2 {
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--prose-heading);
  }

  .scroll-hint {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1rem !important;
    color: var(--prose-muted);
  }

  .explorer-outro {
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .scroll-container {
    position: relative;
    background: var(--map-bg);
  }

  .map-viewport {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    height: 100dvh;
    width: 100%;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--map-bg);
  }

  .map-layer {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .scroll-spacer {
    height: 800vh;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  /* Mobile portrait: the map letterboxes inside the sticky 100dvh viewport.
     A horizontal timeline anchors the bottom band; the rest reads as page
     padding. Terrain mix-blend-mode + mask is disabled because iOS Safari
     GPU-composites them per frame and the cost is brutal during scroll;
     fall back to a low-opacity plain image so terrain texture still hints
     at relief but doesn't tank perf. */
  @media (max-width: 768px) and (orientation: portrait) {
    .scroll-spacer {
      height: 300vh;
    }
  }

  /* Timeline sidebar */
  .timeline-sidebar {
    position: absolute;
    right: 0;
    top: 0;
    height: 100%;
    width: 48px;
    z-index: 20;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease, width 0.2s ease;
    cursor: grab;
    touch-action: none;
  }

  .timeline-sidebar.visible {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .timeline-sidebar:hover {
    width: 56px;
  }

  .timeline-track {
    position: absolute;
    right: 0;
    top: 10%;
    bottom: 10%;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .timeline-track::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    right: 14px;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 1px;
    background: var(--text-secondary);
    opacity: 0.3;
  }

  .timeline-year {
    position: absolute;
    right: 22px;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    white-space: nowrap;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .timeline-tick {
    position: absolute;
    right: 9px;
    width: 10px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--text-secondary);
    opacity: 0.4;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .timeline-indicator {
    position: absolute;
    right: 6px;
    top: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    transition: top 0.1s ease-out, opacity 0.3s ease;
    pointer-events: none;
    opacity: 0;
  }

  .timeline-date-label {
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--road-highlight);
    white-space: nowrap;
    margin-right: 4px;
  }

  .timeline-indicator-line {
    width: 16px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--road-highlight);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 576px) {
    .timeline-sidebar {
      display: none;
    }
  }

  /* Mobile horizontal timeline — anchors the bottom band of the
     letterboxed map on portrait phones. Hidden on desktop. */
  .mobile-timeline {
    display: none;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) and (orientation: portrait) {
    .mobile-timeline {
      display: block;
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 1.25rem;
      left: 1.5rem;
      right: 1.5rem;
      height: 36px;
      z-index: 20;
      opacity: 0;
      transition: opacity 0.4s ease;
      pointer-events: none;
    }
    .mobile-timeline.visible {
      opacity: 1;
    }
  }
  .mobile-timeline-track {
    position: relative;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    width: 100%;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--text-secondary);
    opacity: 0.4;
  }
  .mobile-timeline-tick {
    position: absolute;
    top: -3px;
    width: 1px;
    height: 7px;
    background: var(--text-secondary);
    opacity: 0.7;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
  }
  .mobile-timeline-year {
    position: absolute;
    top: 8px;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .mobile-timeline-indicator {
    position: absolute;
    top: -6px;
    left: 0;
    width: 2px;
    height: 13px;
    background: var(--road-highlight);
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    transition: left 0.1s ease-out;
  }
  .mobile-timeline-date {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 18px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--road-highlight);
    white-space: nowrap;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  /* Hide native scrollbar when timeline is active */
  html:has(.scroll-container) { scrollbar-width: none; }
  html:has(.scroll-container)::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }

  .loading-msg {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    z-index: 10;
  }

  .loading-msg.hidden {
    display: none;
  }

  /* Canvas renderer + HTML label overlay layer. Both span the
     full sticky viewport. Canvas draws roads/water/terrain; label
     overlay sits on top with absolute positioning, repositioned per
     frame by JS via the same camera transform. */
  #mapCanvas {
    image-rendering: -webkit-optimize-contrast;
  }
  .map-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    pointer-events: none;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  /* Right-edge fade: replaces the old SVG mask. Pure CSS gradient =
     GPU-cheap. Visible only during state phases; JS toggles opacity. */
  .state-edge-fade {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    right: 0;
    width: 14%;
    height: 100%;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--map-bg));
    pointer-events: none;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
    z-index: 5;
  }
  .state-edge-fade.visible {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  /* City labels: HTML overlays positioned per frame. Halo via
     text-shadow rather than SVG paint-order — same look, no SVG. */
  .city-label,
  .state-label {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-family: var(--label-font, 'Inter', sans-serif);
    pointer-events: none;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transform-origin: center center;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
    will-change: transform, opacity;
    line-height: 1.05;
    /* Parchment-colored halo. Multiple offset shadows simulate
       paint-order: stroke (browsers render text-shadow under the fill). */
    text-shadow:
      -2px 0 var(--label-halo), 2px 0 var(--label-halo),
      0 -2px var(--label-halo), 0 2px var(--label-halo),
      -2px -2px var(--label-halo), 2px 2px var(--label-halo),
      -2px 2px var(--label-halo), 2px -2px var(--label-halo);
  }
  .city-label {
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .city-label.visible,
  .state-label.visible {
    opacity: 1;
  }
  .state-label {
    font-family: var(--label-font, 'Roboto', sans-serif);
    font-weight: 300;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .state-label-city {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .state-label-park {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  // ============================================================
  // CANVAS RENDERER
  //
  // The road network never changes after load. Previously this page
  // rasterized 84k+ SVG paths per scroll frame; this version parses
  // every path once into a Path2D, then per frame just calls ctx.stroke
  // on already-parsed paths under a cheap camera transform. Everything
  // expensive happens at init.
  // ============================================================

  // --- Constants ---
  var SVG_PADDING = 40; // Must match export script's PADDING
  var DPR = Math.max(1, Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio || 1, 2));
  var TYPE_KEYS = ['r', '3', 's', 'p', 'm', 't'];

  // Phase boundaries (fraction of total scroll 0–1)
  var PHASES = {
    CITY_REVEAL:  { start: 0,    end: 0.50 },
    CITY_HOLD:    { start: 0.50, end: 0.584 },
    ZOOM_OUT:     { start: 0.584, end: 0.78 },
    STATE_REVEAL: { start: 0.78, end: 0.93 },
    HOLD:         { start: 0.93, end: 1.0  }
  };

  // Stroke styles per layer + per highway type. Widths/opacities are in
  // SVG user units (state coord system); they get scaled by the camera
  // transform so they read correctly at city zoom vs. state zoom.
  var STROKE_STYLES = {
    city: {
      'r': { baseWidth: 0.4, baseOpacity: 0.4, litWidth: 0.9 },
      '3': { baseWidth: 0.7, baseOpacity: 0.7, litWidth: 1.3 },
      's': { baseWidth: 1.0, baseOpacity: 0.7, litWidth: 1.0 },
      'p': { baseWidth: 1.2, baseOpacity: 0.8, litWidth: 1.2 },
      'm': { baseWidth: 1.5, baseOpacity: 0.9, litWidth: 1.5 },
      't': { baseWidth: 1.5, baseOpacity: 0.9, litWidth: 1.5 }
    },
    state: {
      's': { baseWidth: 0.6, baseOpacity: 0.5, litWidth: 1.4 },
      'p': { baseWidth: 1.0, baseOpacity: 0.7, litWidth: 2.0 },
      'm': { baseWidth: 1.5, baseOpacity: 0.9, litWidth: 2.8 },
      't': { baseWidth: 1.5, baseOpacity: 0.8, litWidth: 2.8 }
    }
  };

  // --- DOM refs ---
  var canvas = document.getElementById('mapCanvas');
  var ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
  var mapViewport = document.getElementById('mapViewport');
  var mapOverlay = document.getElementById('mapOverlay');
  var stateEdgeFade = document.getElementById('stateEdgeFade');
  var loadingMsg = document.getElementById('loadingMsg');
  var scrollContainer = document.getElementById('scrollContainer');
  var timelineIndicator = document.getElementById('timelineIndicator');
  var timelineDateLabel = document.getElementById('timelineDateLabel');
  var mobileTimelineIndicator = document.getElementById('mobileTimelineIndicator');
  var mobileTimelineDate = document.getElementById('mobileTimelineDate');
  var cityLabelEls = Array.prototype.slice.call(mapOverlay.querySelectorAll('.city-label'));
  var stateLabelEls = Array.prototype.slice.call(mapOverlay.querySelectorAll('.state-label'));

  // --- Palette (read once from CSS custom properties) ---
  var palette = (function () {
    var s = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement);
    return {
      mapBg: s.getPropertyValue('--map-bg').trim() || '#F2EBDD',
      roadBase: s.getPropertyValue('--road-base').trim() || '#B8A38A',
      roadHighlight: s.getPropertyValue('--road-highlight').trim() || '#1F1208',
      waterFill: s.getPropertyValue('--water-fill').trim() || '#B6CFE0'
    };
  })();

  // --- State ---
  var cityData = null, stateData = null;
  var cityWaterData = null, stateWaterData = null;
  var cityEdges = null, statePaths = null;  // edges: [{t, b}, ...]; paths: [Path2D, ...]
  var cityPaths = null, stateEdges = null;
  var cityWaterPaths = null, stateWaterPaths = null;
  var cityWaterExtensionRect = null;        // {x, y, w, h} in city coords
  var stateWaterExtensionPath = null;       // Path2D in state coords
  var terrainImage = null;

  // ViewBox state ([x, y, w, h])
  var fullStateVB = null;
  var stateDisplayVB = null;
  var cityAreaVB = null;
  var displayedCityVB = null, displayedStateVB = null;
  var cityToStateMatrix = null;             // DOMMatrix (city coords → state coords)

  // Label positions (state coords) — precomputed at load
  var cityLabelStatePositions = [];

  // Bucket reveal counters — replaces per-path .lit class machinery
  var cityLitUntil = 0;
  var stateLitUntil = 0;
  var lastCityBucket = -1, lastStateBucket = -1;

  // Scroll geometry (cached on load/resize, NOT read per frame)
  var cachedScrollTop = 0;
  var cachedScrollRange = 1;

  // Render flags
  var ticking = false;
  var loadedCount = 0;
  var dataReady = false;
  var lastEdgeFadeVisible = false;
  var cssWidth = 0, cssHeight = 0;

  // --- Helpers ---
  function lerp(a, b, t) { return a + (b - a) * t; }

  function phaseProgress(phase, progress) {
    if (progress <= phase.start) return 0;
    if (progress >= phase.end) return 1;
    return (progress - phase.start) / (phase.end - phase.start);
  }

  function interpolateViewBox(from, to, t) {
    return [
      lerp(from[0], to[0], t),
      lerp(from[1], to[1], t),
      lerp(from[2], to[2], t),
      lerp(from[3], to[3], t)
    ];
  }

  function parseViewBox(str) { return str.split(' ').map(Number); }

  // --- Compute where city's geographic extent falls in state SVG coordinates ---
  function computeCityAreaInStateSVG(cityGeo, stateGeo, stateVB) {
    var dataW = stateGeo.east - stateGeo.west;
    var dataH = stateGeo.north - stateGeo.south;
    var availW = stateVB[2] - 2 * SVG_PADDING;
    var availH = stateVB[3] - 2 * SVG_PADDING;
    var scale = Math.min(availW / dataW, availH / dataH);
    var offsetX = SVG_PADDING + (availW - dataW * scale) / 2;
    var offsetY = SVG_PADDING + (availH - dataH * scale) / 2;

    function geoToSVG(lng, lat) {
      var x = (lng - stateGeo.west) * scale + offsetX;
      var y = stateVB[3] - ((lat - stateGeo.south) * scale + offsetY);
      return [x, y];
    }

    var topLeft = geoToSVG(cityGeo.west, cityGeo.north);
    var bottomRight = geoToSVG(cityGeo.east, cityGeo.south);

    return [topLeft[0], topLeft[1], bottomRight[0] - topLeft[0], bottomRight[1] - topLeft[1]];
  }

  // --- Compute the transform to position city SVG paths inside state SVG space ---
  function computeCityToStateTransform(cityGeo, stateGeo, cityVB, stateVB) {
    // Reconstruct city SVG transform parameters
    var cityDataW = cityGeo.east - cityGeo.west;
    var cityDataH = cityGeo.north - cityGeo.south;
    var cityAvailW = cityVB[2] - 2 * SVG_PADDING;
    var cityAvailH = cityVB[3] - 2 * SVG_PADDING;
    var cityScale = Math.min(cityAvailW / cityDataW, cityAvailH / cityDataH);
    var cityOX = SVG_PADDING + (cityAvailW - cityDataW * cityScale) / 2;
    var cityOY = SVG_PADDING + (cityAvailH - cityDataH * cityScale) / 2;

    // Reconstruct state SVG transform parameters
    var stateDataW = stateGeo.east - stateGeo.west;
    var stateDataH = stateGeo.north - stateGeo.south;
    var stateAvailW = stateVB[2] - 2 * SVG_PADDING;
    var stateAvailH = stateVB[3] - 2 * SVG_PADDING;
    var stateScale = Math.min(stateAvailW / stateDataW, stateAvailH / stateDataH);
    var stateOX = SVG_PADDING + (stateAvailW - stateDataW * stateScale) / 2;
    var stateOY = SVG_PADDING + (stateAvailH - stateDataH * stateScale) / 2;

    // City NW corner (cityGeo.west, cityGeo.north) in city SVG coords
    // x = cityOX (west edge of data), y = cityOY (north edge, top of data area after Y-flip)
    // City NW corner in state SVG coords
    var stateNW_x = (cityGeo.west - stateGeo.west) * stateScale + stateOX;
    var stateNW_y = stateVB[3] - ((cityGeo.north - stateGeo.south) * stateScale + stateOY);

    // Uniform scale ratio
    var s = stateScale / cityScale;

    // Translation: statePoint = s * cityPoint + (tx, ty)
    var tx = stateNW_x - s * cityOX;
    var ty = stateNW_y - s * cityOY;

    return { s: s, tx: tx, ty: ty };
  }

  // --- Render water paths into a group element ---
  // --- Parse edges into Path2D objects + a per-type index. Each path
  // string is parsed once at load; render only calls ctx.stroke on the
  // already-parsed Path2D. ---
  function buildPathsAndEdges(data) {
    var paths = new Array(data.edges.length);
    var edges = new Array(data.edges.length);
    var byType = {};
    for (var t = 0; t < TYPE_KEYS.length; t++) byType[TYPE_KEYS[t]] = [];
    for (var i = 0; i < data.edges.length; i++) {
      var e = data.edges[i];
      paths[i] = new Path2D(e.d);
      edges[i] = { t: e.t, b: e.b };
      if (byType[e.t]) byType[e.t].push(i);
    }
    edges._byType = byType;
    return { paths: paths, edges: edges };
  }

  function buildWaterPaths(data) {
    if (!data || !data.paths) return [];
    var out = new Array(data.paths.length);
    for (var i = 0; i < data.paths.length; i++) out[i] = new Path2D(data.paths[i]);
    return out;
  }

  // --- Cached scroll geometry (read once on load + on resize). Replaces
  // getBoundingClientRect per frame, which was a forced layout reflow. ---
  function recomputeScrollGeometry() {
    var rect = scrollContainer.getBoundingClientRect();
    cachedScrollTop = window.scrollY + rect.top;
    cachedScrollRange = Math.max(1, scrollContainer.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight);
  }

  function getScrollProgress() {
    var p = (window.scrollY - cachedScrollTop) / cachedScrollRange;
    return p < 0 ? 0 : (p > 1 ? 1 : p);
  }

  // --- Canvas sizing. CSS size matches the sticky viewport; backing-store
  // pixel size is multiplied by devicePixelRatio so it stays crisp. ---
  function resizeCanvas() {
    var rect = mapViewport.getBoundingClientRect();
    cssWidth = rect.width;
    cssHeight = rect.height;
    canvas.width = Math.round(cssWidth * DPR);
    canvas.height = Math.round(cssHeight * DPR);
    canvas.style.width = cssWidth + 'px';
    canvas.style.height = cssHeight + 'px';
  }

  // --- Timeline ---
  var MONTH_NAMES = ['Jan','Feb','Mar','Apr','May','Jun','Jul','Aug','Sep','Oct','Nov','Dec'];
  var tlStart = 0;
  var tlRange = 0;
  var cityBucketTimes = null;

  function parseDate(dateStr) {
    var parts = dateStr.split('-');
    return new Date(parseInt(parts[0]), parseInt(parts[1]) - 1, parseInt(parts[2]));
  }

  function buildTimeline() {
    var track = document.getElementById('timelineTrack');
    var mobileTrack = document.getElementById('mobileTimelineTrack');

    // Compute full date range from both datasets
    var startDate = parseDate(cityData.bucketDates[0]);
    var endDate = parseDate(cityData.bucketDates[cityData.bucketDates.length - 1]);
    var stStart = parseDate(stateData.bucketDates[0]);
    var stEnd = parseDate(stateData.bucketDates[stateData.bucketDates.length - 1]);
    if (stStart < startDate) startDate = stStart;
    if (stEnd > endDate) endDate = stEnd;

    tlStart = startDate.getTime();
    tlRange = endDate.getTime() - tlStart;

    // Precompute city bucket timestamps for click-to-scroll
    cityBucketTimes = [];
    for (var i = 0; i < cityData.bucketDates.length; i++) {
      cityBucketTimes.push(parseDate(cityData.bucketDates[i]).getTime());
    }

    // Year labels — sidebar uses `top` (vertical), mobile uses `left`
    // (horizontal). Same fraction in both cases.
    var startYear = startDate.getFullYear();
    var endYear = endDate.getFullYear();
    for (var y = startYear + 1; y <= endYear; y++) {
      var yearTime = new Date(y, 0, 1).getTime();
      var frac = (yearTime - tlStart) / tlRange;
      if (frac < 0 || frac > 1) continue;

      var label = document.createElement('div');
      label.className = 'timeline-year';
      label.textContent = String(y);
      label.style.top = (frac * 100) + '%';
      track.appendChild(label);

      var mLabel = document.createElement('div');
      mLabel.className = 'mobile-timeline-year';
      mLabel.textContent = String(y);
      mLabel.style.left = (frac * 100) + '%';
      mobileTrack.appendChild(mLabel);
    }

    // Monthly tick marks (skip January — year label already there)
    var cur = new Date(startDate.getFullYear(), startDate.getMonth() + 1, 1);
    while (cur < endDate) {
      var frac = (cur.getTime() - tlStart) / tlRange;
      if (frac >= 0 && frac <= 1 && cur.getMonth() !== 0) {
        var tick = document.createElement('div');
        tick.className = 'timeline-tick';
        tick.style.top = (frac * 100) + '%';
        track.appendChild(tick);

        var mTick = document.createElement('div');
        mTick.className = 'mobile-timeline-tick';
        mTick.style.left = (frac * 100) + '%';
        mobileTrack.appendChild(mTick);
      }
      cur = new Date(cur.getFullYear(), cur.getMonth() + 1, 1);
    }

    document.getElementById('timelineSidebar').classList.add('visible');
    document.getElementById('mobileTimeline').classList.add('visible');
  }

  function updateTimeline(dateStr) {
    if (!dateStr || !tlRange) {
      timelineIndicator.style.opacity = '0';
      mobileTimelineIndicator.style.opacity = '0';
      return;
    }
    var date = parseDate(dateStr);
    var frac = (date.getTime() - tlStart) / tlRange;
    frac = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, frac));
    var label = MONTH_NAMES[date.getMonth()] + ' ' + date.getFullYear();
    timelineIndicator.style.top = (frac * 100) + '%';
    timelineIndicator.style.opacity = '1';
    timelineDateLabel.textContent = label;
    mobileTimelineIndicator.style.left = (frac * 100) + '%';
    mobileTimelineIndicator.style.opacity = '1';
    mobileTimelineDate.textContent = label;
  }

  function setupTimelineInteraction() {
    var sidebar = document.getElementById('timelineSidebar');
    var track = document.getElementById('timelineTrack');
    var isDragging = false;

    function getDateFracFromY(clientY) {
      var rect = track.getBoundingClientRect();
      var frac = (clientY - rect.top) / rect.height;
      return Math.max(0, Math.min(1, frac));
    }

    function scrollToDateFraction(frac) {
      var targetTime = tlStart + frac * tlRange;
      // Find nearest city bucket
      var bestIdx = 0;
      var bestDist = Infinity;
      for (var i = 0; i < cityBucketTimes.length; i++) {
        var dist = Math.abs(cityBucketTimes[i] - targetTime);
        if (dist < bestDist) {
          bestDist = dist;
          bestIdx = i;
        }
      }
      // Map to scroll position in city phase
      var bucketFrac = bestIdx / (cityData.bucketCount - 1);
      var scrollProgress = PHASES.CITY_REVEAL.start + bucketFrac * (PHASES.CITY_REVEAL.end - PHASES.CITY_REVEAL.start);
      // Convert to absolute scroll position
      var containerPageTop = window.pageYOffset + scrollContainer.getBoundingClientRect().top;
      var scrollableHeight = scrollContainer.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
      window.scrollTo(0, containerPageTop + scrollProgress * scrollableHeight);
    }

    sidebar.addEventListener('pointerdown', function(e) {
      isDragging = true;
      sidebar.setPointerCapture(e.pointerId);
      sidebar.style.cursor = 'grabbing';
      document.body.style.userSelect = 'none';
      scrollToDateFraction(getDateFracFromY(e.clientY));
      e.preventDefault();
    });

    sidebar.addEventListener('pointermove', function(e) {
      if (!isDragging) return;
      scrollToDateFraction(getDateFracFromY(e.clientY));
    });

    sidebar.addEventListener('pointerup', function() {
      isDragging = false;
      sidebar.style.cursor = '';
      document.body.style.userSelect = '';
    });

    sidebar.addEventListener('lostpointercapture', function() {
      isDragging = false;
      sidebar.style.cursor = '';
      document.body.style.userSelect = '';
    });
  }

  // --- Phase-based scroll update ---
  // --- Camera: maps scroll progress to view state.
  // Returns the current visible viewBox + per-layer opacities + flags.
  // Pure function: no DOM writes here. ---
  function computeCamera(progress) {
    var phase, visibleVB, zoomDim = false, cityWaterExtensionVisible = false;
    var opacities = {
      cityEdges: 0, cityWater: 0, cityLabels: 0,
      stateEdges: 0, stateWater: 0, stateTerrain: 0, stateLabels: 0
    };

    if (progress <= PHASES.CITY_HOLD.end) {
      phase = 'city';
      visibleVB = displayedCityVB;
      opacities.cityEdges = 1;
      opacities.cityWater = 1;
      opacities.cityLabels = 1;
      cityWaterExtensionVisible = true;
    } else if (progress <= PHASES.ZOOM_OUT.end) {
      phase = 'zoom';
      var t = phaseProgress(PHASES.ZOOM_OUT, progress);
      visibleVB = interpolateViewBox(displayedCityVB, displayedStateVB, t);
      opacities.cityEdges = 1 - t;
      opacities.cityLabels = 1 - t;
      opacities.cityWater = 0;
      opacities.stateEdges = t;
      opacities.stateWater = 1;
      opacities.stateTerrain = t;
      opacities.stateLabels = t;
      zoomDim = true;
    } else {
      phase = 'state';
      visibleVB = displayedStateVB;
      opacities.stateEdges = 1;
      opacities.stateWater = 1;
      opacities.stateTerrain = 1;
      opacities.stateLabels = 1;
    }

    return {
      phase: phase,
      visibleVB: visibleVB,
      opacities: opacities,
      cityWaterExtensionVisible: cityWaterExtensionVisible,
      zoomDim: zoomDim
    };
  }

  // --- Bucket reveal counters. No DOM writes — the next render frame
  // colors paths based on these numbers. ---
  function updateBuckets(progress) {
    var newCityBucket = -1;
    var newStateBucket = -1;
    if (progress <= PHASES.CITY_REVEAL.end) {
      var tc = phaseProgress(PHASES.CITY_REVEAL, progress);
      newCityBucket = Math.min(Math.floor(tc * cityData.bucketCount), cityData.bucketCount - 1);
    } else {
      newCityBucket = cityData.bucketCount - 1;
    }
    if (progress > PHASES.ZOOM_OUT.end) {
      var ts = phaseProgress(PHASES.STATE_REVEAL, progress);
      newStateBucket = Math.min(Math.floor(ts * stateData.bucketCount), stateData.bucketCount - 1);
    }

    cityLitUntil = newCityBucket + 1;   // edges with b < cityLitUntil are lit
    stateLitUntil = newStateBucket + 1;

    // Timeline indicator: only update on bucket change (cheap).
    if (progress <= PHASES.CITY_HOLD.end) {
      if (newCityBucket !== lastCityBucket) {
        if (newCityBucket >= 0) updateTimeline(cityData.bucketDates[newCityBucket]);
        lastCityBucket = newCityBucket;
      }
    } else if (progress > PHASES.ZOOM_OUT.end) {
      if (newStateBucket !== lastStateBucket) {
        if (newStateBucket >= 0) updateTimeline(stateData.bucketDates[newStateBucket]);
        lastStateBucket = newStateBucket;
      }
    } else {
      // Zoom-out: hide indicator
      if (timelineIndicator.style.opacity !== '0') {
        timelineIndicator.style.opacity = '0';
        mobileTimelineIndicator.style.opacity = '0';
      }
    }
  }

  // --- Stroke all edges of a kind in two passes (unlit + lit), grouped
  // by highway type. strokeStyle + lineWidth are set ONCE per type pass,
  // not per edge — the inner loop is just ctx.stroke(Path2D). ---
  function drawEdges(edges, paths, litUntil, opacity, zoomDim, kind) {
    var styles = STROKE_STYLES[kind];
    var byType = edges._byType;
    ctx.lineCap = 'round';
    ctx.lineJoin = 'round';

    // Pass 1: unlit (base color, per-type width and opacity)
    ctx.strokeStyle = palette.roadBase;
    for (var k = 0; k < TYPE_KEYS.length; k++) {
      var typeKey = TYPE_KEYS[k];
      var st = styles[typeKey];
      if (!st) continue;
      var indices = byType[typeKey];
      if (!indices || !indices.length) continue;
      ctx.lineWidth = st.baseWidth;
      ctx.globalAlpha = opacity * st.baseOpacity;
      for (var i = 0; i < indices.length; i++) {
        var idx = indices[i];
        var e = edges[idx];
        if (e.b >= 0 && e.b < litUntil) continue;
        ctx.stroke(paths[idx]);
      }
    }

    // Pass 2: lit (highlight color, or base color if dimmed during zoom-out)
    if (litUntil > 0) {
      ctx.strokeStyle = zoomDim ? palette.roadBase : palette.roadHighlight;
      var litAlpha = zoomDim ? 0.5 : 0.9;
      for (var k = 0; k < TYPE_KEYS.length; k++) {
        var typeKey = TYPE_KEYS[k];
        var st = styles[typeKey];
        if (!st) continue;
        var indices = byType[typeKey];
        if (!indices || !indices.length) continue;
        ctx.lineWidth = zoomDim ? st.baseWidth : st.litWidth;
        ctx.globalAlpha = opacity * litAlpha;
        for (var i = 0; i < indices.length; i++) {
          var idx = indices[i];
          var e = edges[idx];
          if (e.b < 0 || e.b >= litUntil) continue;
          ctx.stroke(paths[idx]);
        }
      }
    }
    ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
  }

  function drawWater(paths, opacity, includeCityExtension) {
    if (!paths.length && !includeCityExtension) return;
    ctx.globalAlpha = opacity;
    ctx.fillStyle = palette.waterFill;
    if (includeCityExtension && cityWaterExtensionRect) {
      var r = cityWaterExtensionRect;
      ctx.fillRect(r.x, r.y, r.w, r.h);
    }
    for (var i = 0; i < paths.length; i++) ctx.fill(paths[i], 'evenodd');
    ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
  }

  function drawStateWaterExtension(opacity) {
    if (!stateWaterExtensionPath) return;
    ctx.globalAlpha = opacity;
    ctx.fillStyle = palette.waterFill;
    ctx.fill(stateWaterExtensionPath, 'evenodd');
    ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
  }

  // --- Position HTML labels: their state-coord position is mapped to
  // CSS pixels via the same camera transform used for canvas drawing. ---
  function positionLabels(camera, sCanvas, txCanvas, tyCanvas) {
    var i, el, sx, sy, cssX, cssY;
    var showCity = camera.opacities.cityLabels > 0.01;
    var showState = camera.opacities.stateLabels > 0.01;

    for (i = 0; i < cityLabelEls.length; i++) {
      el = cityLabelEls[i];
      if (showCity) {
        var pos = cityLabelStatePositions[i];
        if (pos) {
          cssX = (pos.x * sCanvas + txCanvas) / DPR;
          cssY = (pos.y * sCanvas + tyCanvas) / DPR;
          el.style.transform = 'translate(' + cssX + 'px, ' + cssY + 'px) translate(-50%, -50%)';
          el.style.opacity = camera.opacities.cityLabels;
        }
      } else if (el.style.opacity !== '0') {
        el.style.opacity = '0';
      }
    }

    for (i = 0; i < stateLabelEls.length; i++) {
      el = stateLabelEls[i];
      if (showState) {
        sx = parseFloat(el.dataset.sx);
        sy = parseFloat(el.dataset.sy);
        cssX = (sx * sCanvas + txCanvas) / DPR;
        cssY = (sy * sCanvas + tyCanvas) / DPR;
        el.style.transform = 'translate(' + cssX + 'px, ' + cssY + 'px) translate(-50%, -50%)';
        el.style.opacity = camera.opacities.stateLabels;
      } else if (el.style.opacity !== '0') {
        el.style.opacity = '0';
      }
    }
  }

  // --- Main render: one call per scroll frame. ---
  function render(progress) {
    if (!dataReady || !displayedCityVB || !displayedStateVB) return;
    var camera = computeCamera(progress);
    var vb = camera.visibleVB;
    if (!vb) return;

    var cw = canvas.width;
    var ch = canvas.height;
    var aspect = window.innerWidth / window.innerHeight;
    var mode = aspect < 1.0 ? 'meet' : 'slice';
    var scaleX = cw / vb[2];
    var scaleY = ch / vb[3];
    var s = mode === 'meet' ? Math.min(scaleX, scaleY) : Math.max(scaleX, scaleY);
    var tx = (cw - vb[2] * s) / 2 - vb[0] * s;
    var ty = (ch - vb[3] * s) / 2 - vb[1] * s;

    // Reset transform, fill bg
    ctx.setTransform(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0);
    ctx.fillStyle = palette.mapBg;
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, cw, ch);

    // Apply camera (state coords → canvas device pixels)
    ctx.setTransform(s, 0, 0, s, tx, ty);

    // Terrain (under everything else)
    if (camera.opacities.stateTerrain > 0 && terrainImage && terrainImage.complete && terrainImage.naturalWidth > 0) {
      ctx.globalAlpha = camera.opacities.stateTerrain * 0.32;
      ctx.drawImage(terrainImage, 40, 571, 4370, 2308);
      ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
    }

    // State water
    if (camera.opacities.stateWater > 0) {
      drawStateWaterExtension(camera.opacities.stateWater);
      drawWater(stateWaterPaths, camera.opacities.stateWater, false);
    }

    // State edges
    if (camera.opacities.stateEdges > 0) {
      drawEdges(stateEdges, statePaths, stateLitUntil, camera.opacities.stateEdges, camera.zoomDim, 'state');
    }

    // City water + city edges live in city coords; nest cityToStateMatrix
    // on top of the camera transform.
    if (camera.opacities.cityWater > 0 || camera.opacities.cityEdges > 0) {
      ctx.save();
      ctx.transform(
        cityToStateMatrix.a, cityToStateMatrix.b,
        cityToStateMatrix.c, cityToStateMatrix.d,
        cityToStateMatrix.e, cityToStateMatrix.f
      );
      if (camera.opacities.cityWater > 0) {
        drawWater(cityWaterPaths, camera.opacities.cityWater, camera.cityWaterExtensionVisible);
      }
      if (camera.opacities.cityEdges > 0) {
        drawEdges(cityEdges, cityPaths, cityLitUntil, camera.opacities.cityEdges, camera.zoomDim, 'city');
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    // Position labels
    positionLabels(camera, s, tx, ty);

    // Right-edge fade overlay: toggle visibility only on phase change.
    var fadeVisible = camera.phase !== 'city';
    if (fadeVisible !== lastEdgeFadeVisible) {
      lastEdgeFadeVisible = fadeVisible;
      stateEdgeFade.classList.toggle('visible', fadeVisible);
    }
  }

  // --- Scroll handler ---
  function onScroll() {
    if (ticking) return;
    ticking = true;
    requestAnimationFrame(function () {
      var p = getScrollProgress();
      updateBuckets(p);
      render(p);
      ticking = false;
    });
  }

  // --- Load one dataset and start when both ready ---
  // --- Crop a viewBox horizontally to a portrait-leaning aspect (1.2× viewport
  // aspect), centered at `centerFrac` across its width. Mobile portrait only —
  // landscape returns the source VB unchanged. ---
  function cropPortraitVB(sourceVB, centerFrac) {
    var aspect = window.innerWidth / window.innerHeight;
    if (aspect >= 1.0) return sourceVB;
    var fullW = sourceVB[2];
    var fullH = sourceVB[3];
    var cropAspect = aspect * 1.2;
    var newW = fullH * cropAspect;
    if (newW >= fullW) return sourceVB;
    var centerX = sourceVB[0] + fullW * centerFrac;
    return [centerX - newW / 2, sourceVB[1], newW, fullH];
  }

  function computeDisplayedVBs() {
    if (cityAreaVB) displayedCityVB = cropPortraitVB(cityAreaVB, 0.55);
    if (stateDisplayVB) displayedStateVB = cropPortraitVB(stateDisplayVB, 0.555);
  }

  // --- Resize handler: recompute everything that depends on viewport size ---
  function onResize() {
    resizeCanvas();
    computeDisplayedVBs();
    recomputeScrollGeometry();
    if (dataReady) render(getScrollProgress());
  }

  // --- One-time setup after both city + state datasets load ---
  function onMapLoaded() {
    loadedCount++;
    if (loadedCount !== 2) return;

    var cityVB = parseViewBox(cityData.viewBox);
    fullStateVB = parseViewBox(stateData.viewBox);

    // Tight state extent (minus the JSON's padding).
    stateDisplayVB = (function (geo, vb) {
      var dataW = geo.east - geo.west;
      var dataH = geo.north - geo.south;
      var availW = vb[2] - 2 * SVG_PADDING;
      var availH = vb[3] - 2 * SVG_PADDING;
      var scale = Math.min(availW / dataW, availH / dataH);
      var offX = SVG_PADDING + (availW - dataW * scale) / 2;
      var offY = SVG_PADDING + (availH - dataH * scale) / 2;
      return [offX, offY, dataW * scale, dataH * scale];
    })(stateData.geoBounds, fullStateVB);

    cityAreaVB = computeCityAreaInStateSVG(cityData.geoBounds, stateData.geoBounds, fullStateVB);
    computeDisplayedVBs();

    var xform = computeCityToStateTransform(
      cityData.geoBounds, stateData.geoBounds, cityVB, fullStateVB
    );
    cityToStateMatrix = new DOMMatrix([xform.s, 0, 0, xform.s, xform.tx, xform.ty]);

    // Parse all road edges into Path2D arrays + per-type indices. This is
    // the expensive one-time cost; render only calls ctx.stroke on
    // already-parsed paths.
    var stateBuild = buildPathsAndEdges(stateData);
    statePaths = stateBuild.paths;
    stateEdges = stateBuild.edges;

    var cityBuild = buildPathsAndEdges(cityData);
    cityPaths = cityBuild.paths;
    cityEdges = cityBuild.edges;

    // Water polygons (kept in their native coord systems; city water is
    // drawn under the cityToStateMatrix transform).
    stateWaterPaths = buildWaterPaths(stateWaterData);
    cityWaterPaths = buildWaterPaths(cityWaterData);

    // State water extension: L-shape covering Pacific west of the polygon
    // extent + the southwestern strip past the data's south edge.
    var vbW = fullStateVB[2];
    var vbH = fullStateVB[3];
    var extD = 'M' + (-vbW) + ',0 L100,0 L100,2800 L500,2800 L500,' + vbH + ' L' + (-vbW) + ',' + vbH + ' Z';
    stateWaterExtensionPath = new Path2D(extD);

    // City water extension rect — drawn inside cityToStateMatrix so the
    // coords are city-local.
    var cityGeo = cityData.geoBounds;
    var cDataW = cityGeo.east - cityGeo.west;
    var cDataH = cityGeo.north - cityGeo.south;
    var cAvailW = cityVB[2] - 2 * SVG_PADDING;
    var cAvailH = cityVB[3] - 2 * SVG_PADDING;
    var cScale = Math.min(cAvailW / cDataW, cAvailH / cDataH);
    var cOX = SVG_PADDING + (cAvailW - cDataW * cScale) / 2;
    var cOY = SVG_PADDING + (cAvailH - cDataH * cScale) / 2;
    cityWaterExtensionRect = {
      x: -cityVB[2],
      y: 0,
      w: cOX + cityVB[2],
      h: cityVB[3]
    };

    // Pre-compute city label positions in state coords (so render just
    // applies the camera transform). Done at load; recomputed on resize
    // only because cityToStateMatrix doesn't change unless data changes.
    cityLabelStatePositions = cityLabelEls.map(function (el) {
      var lng = parseFloat(el.dataset.lng);
      var lat = parseFloat(el.dataset.lat);
      // lng/lat → city SVG → state SVG via the same transform
      var cx = (lng - cityGeo.west) * cScale + cOX;
      var cy = cityVB[3] - ((lat - cityGeo.south) * cScale + cOY);
      return { x: cx * xform.s + xform.tx, y: cy * xform.s + xform.ty };
    });

    // Pick reasonable CSS font-sizes for HTML labels. The original SVG
    // sized them in viewBox units (cityVB[2] * data-size), which scaled
    // with the camera. For HTML overlays we use fixed CSS px — picked to
    // look right at typical city zoom.
    for (var i = 0; i < cityLabelEls.length; i++) {
      var ratio = parseFloat(cityLabelEls[i].dataset.size) || 0.014;
      cityLabelEls[i].style.fontSize = Math.max(12, ratio * 1100) + 'px';
    }

    dataReady = true;
    loadingMsg.classList.add('hidden');
    buildTimeline();
    setupTimelineInteraction();
    resizeCanvas();
    recomputeScrollGeometry();

    window.addEventListener('scroll', onScroll, { passive: true });
    window.addEventListener('resize', onResize);

    // Initial paint
    updateBuckets(getScrollProgress());
    render(getScrollProgress());
  }

  // --- Init: fetch data, kick everything off ---
  async function init() {
    try {
      var mobile = window.innerWidth / window.innerHeight < 1.0;
      var cityUrl = mobile ? '/assets/data/city-roads.mobile.json' : '/assets/data/city-roads.json';

      var responses = await Promise.all([
        fetch(cityUrl),
        fetch('/assets/data/state-roads.json'),
        fetch('/assets/data/city-water.json'),
        fetch('/assets/data/state-water.json')
      ]);

      // Mobile fallback to full file if the build-time mobile JSON is missing
      if (!responses[0].ok && mobile) {
        responses[0] = await fetch('/assets/data/city-roads.json');
      }
      if (!responses[0].ok) throw new Error('City: HTTP ' + responses[0].status);
      if (!responses[1].ok) throw new Error('State: HTTP ' + responses[1].status);

      cityWaterData = responses[2].ok ? await responses[2].json() : null;
      stateWaterData = responses[3].ok ? await responses[3].json() : null;

      // Load hillshade in parallel (non-blocking); rerender once available.
      terrainImage = new Image();
      terrainImage.src = '/assets/data/state-hillshade.jpg';
      terrainImage.addEventListener('load', function () {
        if (dataReady) render(getScrollProgress());
      });

      cityData = await responses[0].json();
      onMapLoaded();
      stateData = await responses[1].json();
      onMapLoaded();
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error:', error);
      loadingMsg.textContent = 'Error loading data: ' + error.message;
    }
  }

  init();
</script>
